## 5. Evidence Collection and Preservation

### 5.1 Evidence Register

{{ business_name }} must maintain the following evidence for tort defence purposes:

| Evidence Category | Specific Items | Retention Period |
|-------------------|---------------|-----------------|
| Policies and procedures | AI Acceptable Use Policy, Privacy Policy, AI Procurement Policy, Data Classification Policy | Current version + 7 years of prior versions |
| PIAs and risk assessments | All PIAs, AI risk assessments, vendor risk assessments | 7 years from completion |
| Training records | Staff AI training completion records, training materials | 7 years from delivery |
| Consent records | Individual consent forms, opt-in records, cookie consent logs | 7 years from collection or duration of relationship + 7 years |
| Technical controls | Configuration records, access control lists, encryption certificates | 7 years from implementation |
| Incident records | AI incident reports, breach notifications, complaint records | 7 years from resolution |
{% if vendor_dpa_in_place %} | Vendor agreements | DPAs, sub-processor lists, model training opt-out confirmations | Duration of contract + 7 years |{% else %} | **Vendor agreements** | **DPAs not yet in place — critical gap for defence** | Duration of contract + 7 years |{% endif %}
| Decision logs | AI decision outputs, human review records, override logs | 7 years from decision |

### 5.2 Preservation Requirements

- All evidence must be stored in a manner that is **tamper-evident** and **retrievable**
- Electronic records must include metadata (creation date, author, modification history)
- {{ business_name }} must implement a **litigation hold process** that can be activated within 24 hours of receiving a claim
- Backup copies must be stored separately from operational systems

