## 6. Pre-Incident Measures

The following measures should be in place **before** any claim arises:

### 6.1 Policy Framework

- [ ] AI Acceptable Use Policy — current and distributed
- [ ] Privacy Policy — references AI processing specifically
- [ ] AI Procurement Policy — ensures new tools are assessed before deployment
- [ ] Data Classification Policy — AI data is classified and handled accordingly
- [ ] AI Ethics Framework — demonstrates commitment to responsible AI use

### 6.2 Assessments

- [ ] PIA conducted for each AI system processing personal information
{% if pia_conducted %} *Status: Completed*{% else %} **Status: Not yet conducted — remediate immediately**{% endif %}
- [ ] Vendor risk assessments completed for all AI vendors
{% if vendor_audit_rights %} *Status: Vendor audit rights are in place*{% else %} **Status: Vendor audit rights not yet secured**{% endif %}
{% if ai_supply_chain_assessed %}- [ ] AI supply chain risk assessment completed{% else %}- [ ] **AI supply chain risk assessment not yet conducted**{% endif %}

### 6.3 Training

- [ ] All staff completed AI privacy awareness training
- [ ] Staff with AI system access completed role-specific training
- [ ] Training records retained for evidentiary purposes
- [ ] Training content reviewed and updated annually

### 6.4 Technical Safeguards

- [ ] Logging enabled for all AI system interactions
- [ ] Human review available for automated decisions
{% if human_review_available %} *Status: Human review is available*{% else %} **Status: Human review not yet implemented — high priority**{% endif %}
- [ ] Data minimisation controls configured
- [ ] Encryption applied to AI data in transit and at rest

