## 7. Post-Incident Response Checklist

When {{ business_name }} receives a statutory tort claim or becomes aware of a potential claim:

### 7.1 Within 24 Hours

- [ ] Notify {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "the AI governance contact" }}
- [ ] Notify legal counsel (internal or external)
- [ ] Activate litigation hold on all relevant evidence
- [ ] Preserve logs, decision records, and system configurations for the relevant AI system
- [ ] Do **not** modify, retrain, or update the AI system until advised by legal counsel

### 7.2 Within 72 Hours

- [ ] Identify the AI system(s) involved in the claim
- [ ] Retrieve all evidence from the Evidence Register (Section 5)
- [ ] Prepare a timeline of the AI processing at issue
- [ ] Identify all individuals potentially affected (not just the claimant)
{% if ndb_ai_process %}- [ ] Assess NDB obligations using {{ business_name }}'s established AI-specific NDB process{% else %}- [ ] Assess whether a Notifiable Data Breach has also occurred{% endif %}
- [ ] Assess which defence(s) from Section 4 are available

### 7.3 Within 14 Days

- [ ] Complete a full evidence package for legal counsel
- [ ] Document the reasonable steps taken before the incident (Section 6)
- [ ] Identify and address any gaps in defence preparation
- [ ] Prepare a witness list (staff who managed the AI system, conducted PIAs, delivered training)
- [ ] Assess whether voluntary remediation (apology, compensation, system changes) is appropriate

